headline: Bunge Stock Rises on China Export Ban Threat, Despite Lowered Profit Outlook
summary: Shares of agriculture company Bunge Global rose 11% in midday trading Wednesday, the top performer in the S&P 500. The move followed a post from President Trump late Tuesday threatening to ban exports from China of used cooking oil—a key ingredient needed to produce renewable fuels.

headline: Trump's cooking oil embargo would be bullish for these 3 stocks
summary: Tensions between the US and China intensified after President Trump threatened a cooking oil embargo in response to China's refusal to buy US soybeans. The threat is boosting oil-seed processor stocks like Bunge (BG) and ADM (ADM). Heather Jones Research founder and senior analyst, Heather Jones, joins Market Catalysts host Julie Hyman to explain why Bunge, ADM, and Darling Ingredients (DAR) would be the "primary beneficiaries" of such an embargo. To watch more expert insights and analysis on the latest market action, check out more Market Catalysts.
